    <h2>About the Project</h2>
    <p>TinyCongress is a work-in-progress web community platform that enables users to create accounts, manage keys, and participate in polling rooms. Built with modern technologies for a fast, reliable user experience.</p>

    <h2>Core Technologies</h2>
    <div class="tech-stack">
      <div class="tech-item">
        <h3>React Frontend</h3>
        <p>Simple, modern UI built with React and Mantine component library for creating accounts and participating in polling rooms.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tech-item">
        <h3>Rust Backend</h3>
        <p>High-performance GraphQL API powered by axum, tokio, and sqlx, implementing polling room runtime and CRUD operations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tech-item">
        <h3>Kubernetes Development</h3>
        <p>Managed by Skaffold for local dev clusters with hot reload, CI testing, and production image building.</p>
      </div>
